- Always do npm run format on any file you edit.
- Always update the README if your changes affect setup, usage, API contracts, or anything relevant to users/contributors.
- Use global constants for:
  - external/internal API routes  
  - hardcoded numbers (timeouts, limits, etc.)
  - error messages and success messages  
- Always use antd as the primary css components framework
- Always use redux toolkit for global state management and local useStates for managing component level states
- Always do error handling wherever required with optional chaining, try-catch etc
- Please make sure each and every UI component is responsive